    "background": "You are the mayor of the village of Boberkurwa and have to decide whether an area of X square metres should be sealed for a car park for the new primary school. These X square metres are a nature reserve and are currently home to a beaver family. Children from the primary school took part in a Tiktok Challenge in which they tried to catch beavers. During the attempt, they were bitten by the beavers. \nTo avoid admitting that they had harassed the animals, the children claim that the beavers ambushed them after school and bit them unprovoked. \nThe parents' association, which is led by the owner of the village car dealership, is now pleading for the beavers to be shot. The farmers' association, which is made up entirely of hunters, adds that the beavers are an invasive species that endanger the habitats of farm animals (they would also like to have trophies in their collection at the local hunting museum). \nThe village's birding society claims that the bite marks are from cats and refer to their expertise in biology. They argue in favour of a curfew for cats. \nThe Boberkurwa eco-association is firmly against new car parks, claiming that they are not sustainable from a biodynamic point of view and that the village is far too small for people to simply walk to fetch the children from school. They post that the beavers are just the beginning, soon there will be no wild animals at all if they are all shot. \nA local politician from another party believes that the newly arrived family from the big city, who live next door to the school, are to blame for the beavers' aggression. They listen to new-fashioned, loud music and make the beavers very aggressive.",
